<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation author="Murayama, J" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Faculty of Agriculture, Yamaguti University" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="81 - 106" refId="B279" refString="Murayama, J, 1955. Supplementary notes on the scolytid-fauna of Japan. Bulletin of the Faculty of Agriculture, Yamaguti University 6: 81 - 106" title="Supplementary notes on the scolytid-fauna of Japan." volume="6" year="1955">Murayama (1955)</bibRefCitation>
states the type series of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murayama" authorityYear="1955" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stereocaulaceae" genus="Xyleborus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Xyleborus kirishimanus" order="Lecanorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="kirishimanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xyleborus kirishimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is comprised of 21 males. Given the heavily female biased sex ratio and biology of male xyleborines it is dubious that 21 males could have been collected and not a single female. This suspicion was confirmed by examination of four syntypes examined by SMS and AIC, all of which are female.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
